{"version": 2, "width": 80, "height": 24, "timestamp": 1782484576, "idle_time_limit": 2.0, "env": {"SHELL": "/usr/bin/zsh", "TERM": "xterm-256color"}}
[0.004807, "o", "\u001b[36m# An AI agent connects to MCP servers. Each one hands it tools.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m# Which of those tools are a compliance problem, and how do you contain them?\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.506836, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m# Step 1: discover what the agent can actually do\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m$ agentic-compliance-scan --discover mcp-config.json > my-agent.json\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[7.790687, "o", "\u001b[32m"]
[7.79229, "o", "# filesystem: discovered 14 tool(s)\r\n"]
[7.792544, "o", "\u001b[0m\u001b[90m# tools listed and effects classified, no hand-listing.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[10.294721, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m# Step 2: scan against the law, for Germany\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m$ agentic-compliance-scan --inventory my-agent.json --jurisdiction DE\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[10.547048, "o", "11 gap(s) found (high: 6, medium: 5).\r\n## National law (DE)\r\n### [high] Agent acts on an in-scope system with no risk analysis and information system security policies declared\r\n- Reference: NIS2 § 30 Abs. 2 Nr. 1 BSIG, DE BSIG (NIS2UmsuCG 2025)\r\n"]
[13.549284, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m# Step 3: the gateway rules to lock down the dangerous tools\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m$ agentic-compliance-scan --policy my-agent.json\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[14.075308, "o", "## wm-mcp-server:setup_user_management (require human approval)\r\n- webMethods condition: `${request.payload.jsonPath[$.params.name]} == \"setup_user_management\"`\r\n- webMethods action: Invoke webMethods IS service: read the body, hold the call for human approval or reject with status 403\r\n## wm-mcp-server:setup_oauth (require human approval)\r\n- webMethods condition: `${request.payload.jsonPath[$.params.name]} == \"setup_oauth\"`\r\n- webMethods action: Invoke webMethods IS service: read the body, hold the call for human approval or reject with status 403\r\n"]
[17.078111, "o", "\r\n\u001b[33m\u001b[1m# The full loop:\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m# discover a real MCP server, cite the gaps in your own national law,\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m# and generate the gateway policy to close them. In seconds.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m# github.com/cpoder/agentic-compliance-scan\u001b[0m\r\n"]
